3. Functional Requirements  

a. Description (What the InternLink system must do)


3.1 User Management

- FR1 – User Registration
The system shall allow students, companies, university staff, and admins to register using required personal or organizational details.
- FR2 – User Login
The system shall authenticate users using email and password.
- FR3 – Role-Based Access Control
The system shall restrict features based on user type (Student, Company, University Staff, Admin).
- FR4 – Profile Management
Users shall be able to view and update their personal profiles.
- FR5 – Password Recovery
The system shall allow users to recover/reset forgotten passwords via email verification.

3.2 Student Features

- FR6 – View Opportunities
The system shall allow students to browse a list of available internship opportunities.
- FR7 – Search Opportunities
The system shall allow students to search for opportunities based on keywords.
- FR8 – Filter Opportunities
The system shall allow filtering by category, location, company, deadline, and internship type.
- FR9 – View Opportunity Details
The system shall display full information about each opportunity.
- FR10 – Apply to Opportunities
The system shall allow students to apply to an opportunity by submitting required information/documents. (!)
- FR11 – Application Tracking
The system shall allow students to view the status of their submitted applications (Pending, Reviewed, Accepted, Rejected).

3.3 Company Features

- FR12 – Post Opportunity
Companies shall be able to create and submit internship listings.
- FR13 – Edit Opportunity
Companies shall be able to update details of their posted opportunities.
- FR14 – Delete Opportunity
Companies shall be able to delete their posted opportunities.
- FR15 – View Verification Status
Companies shall be able to see whether their posted opportunities are Approved, Rejected, or Pending.
- FR16 – Manage Company Profile
Companies shall be able to update company details.

3.4 University Staff Features

- FR17 – Review Submitted Opportunities
University staff shall access a list of opportunities marked as “Pending”.
- FR18 – Approve or Reject Opportunities
Staff shall be able to Approve or Reject opportunities posted by companies.


3.5 Admin Features

- FR19 – Manage Users
Admin shall be able to view all users and filter by role.
- FR20 – Enable/Disable Accounts
Admin shall be able to activate or deactivate any user account. (?)
- FR21 – Moderate Opportunities
Admin shall be able to approve, reject, edit, or delete any posted opportunity. (?)
- FR22 – Monitor System Activity
Admin shall access an analytics dashboard displaying key stats (number of users, opportunities, applications).
- FR23 – Assign Roles
Admin shall be able to update or change user roles.

3.6 System Feature

- FR24 – Dashboard Display
The system shall provide personalized dashboards for each role (Student, Company, University Staff, Admin) (Simple?)
- FR25 – Pagination for Listings
The system shall paginate long lists (opportunities, users, applications).
- FR26 – Database Storage
The system shall store all users, opportunities, and applications in a secure database.
- FR27 – API Integration
The system shall use backend APIs for all data communication between frontend and backend.
- FR28 – Security Requirements
The system shall protect user data with authentication tokens, validation, and secure endpoints. 

